  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>flat white</strong> <strong>mushroom[s]</strong> and <strong>baby button mushrooms </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1687523430635-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1687523430635-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1687523430635-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1687523430635-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1687523430635-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot (with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>sliced mushrooms </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-6 min or until the onion is softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675164434433-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675164434433-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675164434433-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675164434433-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675164434433-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion and mushrooms are cooking, peel your <strong>potato[es] </strong>and chop into very small pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675164437700-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675164437700-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675164437700-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675164437700-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675164437700-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min or until fragrant, then once fragrant, add your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>to the pan with 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[850ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a medium-high heat and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the potato is fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1675164441210-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1675164441210-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1675164441210-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1675164441210-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1675164441210-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the soup is cooking, combine a generous knob of<strong> butter </strong>in a bowl with the <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>dried oregano</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>and mix it all together – this is your <strong>garlic butter</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1675164444567-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1675164444567-x400.jpg",
