      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your<strong> ciabatta[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Spread the <strong>garlic butter </strong>over the<strong> </strong>ciabatta halves and add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>buttered ciabatta</strong> to one side of a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Tear the <strong>remaining buttered ciabatta</strong> into bite-sized pieces and add to the other side of the tray[s]</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 5-7 min or until golden and crusty – this is your<strong> garlic bread </strong>and <strong>croutons</strong></p>",
